Chainlink operates at the speed of the underlying blockchain, this is indeed initially Ethereum (13 sec blocks), but requests can be synchronous  It is blockchain agnostic and is being built to support Polkadot, Cosmos, Irisnet, Hedera, EVM chains, substrate chains, and many more  https://t.co/RHXcFVzCUb

I'm not against competition and welcome innovation. But it's easy to make statements about why you're the best, yet substantially more difficult to actually make things happen in the real world. Chainlink's been working on the oracle problem since 2014, most others just started.

Chainlink oracle networks update on a deviation threshold (e.g. every 0.5% deviation since last update), on a heartbeat (e.g. at least every ten mins) or a mixture of the two (every 1% and once an hour)  This is all customizable and is different for every project's exact needs  https://t.co/K3SY8PnhCQ
